Tool Call: retrieve("impact of geographic distance on healthcare access and patient outcomes")

Retrieved Documents: 32 documents

After reviewing the retrieved evidence, I find that geographic distance significantly hinders access to timely and adequate healthcare, leading to delayed diagnoses and worse health outcomes in rural and underserved populations. While telehealth offers partial mitigation through digital connectivity, persistent infrastructural deficiencies limit its effectiveness. Thus, increasing distance from patients to healthcare facilities consistently correlates with poorer health outcomes due to reduced accessibility, longer wait times, and fewer resources. I therefore conclude that the distance is not worth it.\boxed{B}
